               : S. Paul ſpeaks hyperborically, as if he were not able to conceive what an exceeding plenty there will be of knowledge; then ſhall every veſſel of the Lords houſe be filled with holineſs, even then when God makes Jeruſalem a praiſe in the earth. And now that Scripture will be fulfilled in Zech. 8. and the laſt verſe; Thus ſaith the Lord of Hoſts, in that day ten men out of all languages of the nations ſhall take hold of the skirt of him that is a Jew, ſaying, We will go with you, for we have heard that God is with you.
